      • readUntil

        public static boolean readUntil(java.io.InputStream stream,
                                char ch1,
                                char ch2)
        Consumes the stream until a character provided as a parameter is encountered. This is not case sensitive. Returns true if the first provided parameter is encountered and false if it is the second. If end of file is encountered false shall be returned. If the input parameters are the same, true is returned if it is encountered.
        Parameters:
        stream - the input stream
        ch1 - the first character to match
        ch2 - the second character to match
        Returns:
        whether the first or second character parameter is encountered first

      • skipSpace

        public static char skipSpace(java.io.InputStream stream,
                             char ch)
        Consumes an input stream until a non whitespace character is consumed. If this character is not the same as the input character, the character is returned, else the lowest character value is provided.
        Parameters:
        stream - the input stream
        ch - the character which returns will lowest character value
        Returns:
        the non whitespace character encountered or the lowest character value should it match the input parameter

      • readString

        public static java.lang.String readString(java.io.InputStream stream,
                                          char c1,
                                          char c2)
        Consumes the input stream until either one of the parameters are encountered. Encounters are case sensitive. If the first parameter is encountered, a String containing the characters read is returned. Otherwise the null string is returned.The parameter found is not returned at the end of the String. If end of file is encountered the null string is returned.
        Parameters:
        stream - the input stream
        c1 - the character that, once encountered, returns the String of chars up to this point, including the last parameter
        c2 - the character that, once encountered, returns the null string.
        Returns:
        the String of chars leading up to the first parameter, or null if the second parameter was encountered.

      • readStringUntilWhitespace

        public static java.lang.String readStringUntilWhitespace(java.io.InputStream stream,
                                                         char ch)
        Consumes the input stream building a string of all values until either whitespace or the input parameter is found. The final parameter is not returned. Returns null if the end of file was encountered before the parameters.
        Parameters:
        stream - the input stream
        ch - the character which stops the stream being consumed
        Returns:
        the String of all chars encountered until the whitespace or parameter was encountered
